The paper proposes a machine learning system for EEG analysis, which involves sequential decoding and deep learning networks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of deep learning networks for postprocessing, which suggests that computer vision (cs.CV) may also be a relevant sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the potential clinical applications of the proposed system, which suggests that human-computer interaction (cs.HC) may also be a relevant sub-category.
